# ZenoSIM / EvairSIM — Business Context

## Company

- Sells **eSIMs and physical SIMs** to retail (B2C) and enterprise (B2B) customers worldwide.
- Operates two consumer-facing storefronts:
  - **H5 web app** (`Evair-H5`, React/Vite, hosted on Netlify) — primary today
  - **Native Flutter app** (`EvairSIM-App`, lives at `/Users/jordanmok/Development/EvairSIM-App`) — in development, mirrors H5 features
- Operates one internal portal:
  - **Admin** (`admin`, Vue 3 + Element Plus) — staff portal for catalogue, pricing, orders, customer ops
- One backend:
  - **Laravel API** (`Evair-Laravel`) — single source of truth; both H5 and APP fetch from it; admin writes to it.
- Brand color `#FF6600` (orange). Domain `evairdigital.com`. Support `service@evairdigital.com`.
- China dev team uses Aliyun Codeup; founder mirrors to GitHub + iCloud Drive weekly auto-backup.

## Suppliers (the two that matter)

| Aspect | **PCCW** (`supplier_id = 1`) | **RED TEA** / eSIMAccess (`supplier_id = 2`) |
|---|---|---|
| Plan model | Flexible — traffic policies, post-activation policy swap | **Fixed** — data + days + region locked at activation |
| Cost model | Variable, per-MB / per-policy | **Fixed cost locked at activation time** |
| Editable in admin | Markup, traffic policy, bundle composition | **Markup only** (cost is supplier-locked) |
| Refund of activated SIM | Possible (re-credit) | **Not possible** — supplier cost non-recoverable |
| Used for | Variable enterprise plans, regional bundles | Standard retail eSIM catalogue (most SKUs) |

## Products

- **eSIM** — every country (~207, 2,489+ packages from RED TEA). Sold in H5 + APP.
  - GSMA standard: profile installs **once** from SM-DP+. If user deletes, must re-purchase.
- **Physical SIM** — **US data plans only** (today). Uses eUICC + ARA-M; profiles can be re-flashed by carrier.
  - Activation in H5 = binding only (associate card + login). Factory pre-writes the profile.
- **Recharge / Top-up** — both PCCW and RED TEA recharge plans available; managed in admin under each supplier group.
- **Marketplaces** — physical SIMs also sold on Amazon.com and Temu.com; same H5 binding flow.

## Data flow rule (security)

**All supplier APIs MUST be called by the Laravel backend. H5 and APP must never call Red Tea / PCCW directly.**

- Reason: prevents supplier credentials/SKU leaks, lets admin team control plans/prices/visibility centrally.
- H5 and APP fetch product catalogue from `/v1/h5/packages*` (Laravel).
- Admin writes via `/v1/admin/supplier-packages*` (Laravel).
- Migration in progress: H5 catalogue migrated; APP catalogue migrated; legacy direct supplier calls being removed.

## Customer segments

- **个人客户 (B2C)** — retail consumers. Default segment.
- **企业客户 (B2B)** — enterprise tenants. Restricted admin access (see `admin/src/api/modules/login.ts` `B2B_ALLOWED_PATHS`).
- B2B customers see only: `首页`, `销售运营 › 销售额报表`, `客户管理 › 企业客户` and its subpages.

## Languages

- H5 + APP: en (primary), zh, es. Every user-facing string must use `t()` keys.
- Admin: zh primary; en for ops/dev fallback.
